@Node INTRODUCTION
@TITLE Introduction

 @{u}So what does it do ?@{uu}

 InfoWin is a tiny program mainly to be used in AmigaDOS batch scripts.
 It opens a small, borderless window showing a message.

@EndNode

@Node REQUIREMENTS "Requirements"

 The binary for AmigaOS/68K requires:

  · AmigaOS/68K >= 2.04 (V36) or AROS/68K
  · CPU >= 68020
  · MUI >= 3.8 (@{"Download" rxs "IF ~SHOW('L','openurl.library') THEN CALL ADDLIB('openurl.library',3,-66);url='http://main.aminet.net/util/libs/mui38usr.lha';OpenURL(url,SHOW,TOFRONT,NEWWIN,LAUNCH);EXIT" })

 The MorphOS binary requires:

  · MorphOS/PPC >= 0.4
  · any PPC CPU

 Both versions additionally need:

  · BWin.mcc (@{"Download" rxs "IF ~SHOW('L','openurl.library') THEN CALL ADDLIB('openurl.library',3,-66);url='http://main.aminet.net/dev/mui/MCC_BWin.lha';OpenURL(url,SHOW,TOFRONT,NEWWIN,LAUNCH);EXIT" })
  · optional InfoText.mcc (für FANCY Option) (@{"Download" rxs "IF ~SHOW('L','openurl.library') THEN CALL ADDLIB('openurl.library',3,-66);url='http://www.diku.dk/hjemmesider/studerende/benny/archives/MCC_InfoText.LHA';OpenURL(url,SHOW,TOFRONT,NEWWIN,LAUNCH);EXIT" })
  · optional MUI 4

@Endnode

@Node INSTALLATION
@TITLE Installation

 Automatically:

  Use the supplied Installer script

 Manually:

  Copy AmigaOS_68K/C/InfoWin oder MorphOS/C/InfoWin to C:

  Copy Locale/Catalogs/Deutsch/MyNotes.catalog to Locale:Catalogs/Deutsch

  Copy Locale/Help/English/MyNotes.guide to Help:English

  Copy Locale/Help/Deutsch/MyNotes.guide to Help:Deutsch

@EndNode

@Node USAGE
@TITLE Usage

 Usage:

 TIMEOUT/N/K,FANCY/S,MESSAGE=MSG/F/A

 TIMEOUT/N/K     maximum time to wait in seconds (defaults to forever).

 FANCY/S         activate fancy look.

 MESSAGE=MSG/F/A message to be displayed in the window. This argument must be
                 provided. If the text includes spaces you need to enclose it with "".
                 You can include special formatting codes into the string, which will be
                 interpreted as follows:

                 *n                Starts a new line; so you can have multiline message text.
                 ESC u             Switch on underlined text style.
                 ESC b             Switch on bold text style.
                 ESC i             Switch on italic text style.
                 ESC n             Switches back to normal text style.
                 ESC c             Switch on centered justification. Only valid at the
                                   beginning of the string or after a newline.
                 ESC l             Switch on left justification. Only valid at the
                                   beginning of the string or after a newline.
                 ESC r             Switch on right justification. Only valid at the
                                   beginning of the string or after a newline.
                 ESC I[5:filename] Include an image. You must provide the filename here.
                                   If the filename contains spaces you must enclose it
                                   with "" resp.*" *" (see below). AmigaOS' datatypes system
                                   is used for loading.
                 ESC x             Set text color to pen x , where x is between 2 and 9.
                 ESC -             Switch off special character parsing.

                 If you start InfoWin from the command line (from a shell,
                 from an AmigaDOS batch file, or in DOpus as AmigaDOS command,...),
                 ESC is represented by *e, a " within a string enclosed by "" is repre-
                 sented by *". Look at the AmigaDOS documentation for further info.


 ?               Shows above template and asks you for input. If you provide a ? again, you
                 will get a long description (/this) text.


 Example:

  InfoWin TIMEOUT=10 FANCY "*ecInstallation finished *ebsuccessfully*en !*n*nHave some fun with it !"

 Shows for a maximum of 10 seconds a borderless information window. The two lined text is displayed centered.
 The user can abort the window using ESC.

 If you start InfoWin with @{b}?@{ub} as argument AmigaDOS will show you the template
 and ask you for input. If you again input a @{b}?@{ub} you will get a more detailed explanation
 of the arguments.

 You can cancel InfoWin by sending a CTRL_C break. This can be done by pressing
 <Ctrl><c> or by the following commandline:

  break `status COM=InfoWin` C

 Note that it can take up to one second for the program to quit.

 If you call it with incorrect or missing arguments, an error code of 161 will be raised.

@Endnode

@Node REXX "Rexx"

 InfoWin has an ARexx-Port.

 Its name is INFOWIN.x, whereas x is the number of the running instance of InfoWin.
 So if you have it running three times at the same time it's INFOWIN.1,
 INFOWIN.2, ...

 Besides the commands, every MUI application has (have a look at the @{"MUI User Guide" link HELP:English/MUI.guide/USE_AREXX} for further info),
 InfoWin has one application specific Rexx command:

  SetMessage MESSAGE/A

 It allows you to change the displayed text at runtime.

 Template:

 MESSAGE/A message to be displayed in the window. This argument must be
           provided. If the text includes spaces you need to enclose it with "".
           You can include special formatting codes into the string, which will be
           interpreted as follows:
             *n              Starts a new line; so you can have multiline message text.
             *eu             Switch on underlined text style.
             *eb             Switch on bold text style.
             *ei             Switch on italic text style.
             *en             Switches back to normal text style.
             *ec             Switch on centered justification. Only valid at the
                             beginning of the string or after a newline.
             *el             Switch on left justification. Only valid at the
                             beginning of the string or after a newline.
             *er             Switch on right justification. Only valid at the
                             beginning of the string or after a newline.
             *eI[5:filename] Include an image. You must provide the filename here.
                             If the filename contains spaces you must enclose it
                             with "". AmigaOS' datatypes system is used for loading.
             *ex             Set text color to pen x , where x is between 2 and 9.
             *e-             Switch off special character parsing.


 Example:

  see Rexx/test.rexx

@EndNode

